# Code Audit (March 2026)

Full audit completed 2026-03-25 across all 115 Swift source files. Branch: `audit/code-cleanup-mar25`.

**Why:** User requested thorough review for bugs, security risks, storage leaks, and code quality — no UI changes allowed.

**How to apply:** If merging the audit branch, verify all 14 batches compiled cleanly. If starting fresh, check the deferred items below for known tech debt.

## Completed (14 batches)

**Security:**
- Password comparison bug fixed (`ContentView.swift:2874`) — was using `==` instead of `KeychainManager.verifyPassword`
- Backup restore now throws instead of silently swallowing `try?` errors (`BackupManager.swift`)
- Force-unwrap on Formspree URL replaced with `guard let` (`FloatingSettings.swift`)
- Sparkle `SUEnableAutomaticChecks` set to `false` — feed URL is still a placeholder (`your-host.com`)

**Code quality:**
- 50+ NSLog statements removed across 6 files, replaced with `Logger` for error paths
- 2 force casts (`as!`) converted to safe `as?` guards
- 3 `try!` regex inits converted to `try?` in WebMetadataFetcher
- `[weak self]` added to Task closures in BackupManager and ImageStorageManager
- Dead `NoteEntity.wordCount` property removed

**Storage:**
- `cleanupUnusedImages` hooked up on initial load (was defined but never called)
- `ThumbnailCache.cleanupOrphanedThumbnails` added and hooked up on initial load
- `NoteVersionManager` capped at 50 versions per note

**Performance:**
- `recomputeDerivedNotes` rewritten from 9 sort passes to 1 sort + 1 partition pass

**Build config:**
- `ENABLE_USER_SELECTED_FILES` aligned to `readwrite` to match entitlement

